Andy Murray secures fourth Queen's title with two wins in a day
Watch five key points that helped Andy Murray win a record-equalling fourth Queen's club title in his 6-3 6-4 victory over Kevin Anderson.The British number one joins four-time winners including John McEnroe and Boris Becker after a brilliant performance that brought him victory in just 64 minutes.Murray, the top seed, had earlier finished a rain delayed semi-final,beating Viktor Troicki 6-3 7-6 (7-4).Available to UK users only